# .vercelignore — CLASS 3 REFERENCE TEMPLATE
#
# Goes in the ROOT of your project (next to package.json). This is the file
# that keeps the dual-web split clean on the Vercel side.
#
# WHY IT MATTERS: your human site deploys to Vercel; your bot surface (the llm/
# folder) is served by Cloudflare Pages, and the Worker source (infra/) is a
# deploy artifact — NEITHER should be bundled into the Vercel human-site deploy.
# Without this file, Vercel may try to include or serve those folders, muddying
# the separation the dual-web architecture depends on. Listing them here makes
# Vercel ignore them entirely.
#
# Claude: copy this to the project root. Keep the /llm/ and /infra/ lines — they
# are the load-bearing ones. Add any other build/tooling folders the project has.

# Bot surface — served by Cloudflare Pages, NOT Vercel
/llm/

# Cloudflare Worker source — a deploy artifact, not human-site web content
/infra/

# Internal tooling / config / docs (never part of the deployed human site)
/.claude/
/scripts/
/logs/

# Reference/planning docs
/ARCHITECTURE.md
